  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {C}}\xrightarrow {U}{\mathcal {D}}]]></fr:tex> be a functor and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I}]]></fr:tex> be a category. The functor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> is said to <fr:em>create (co)limits of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I}]]></fr:tex>-figures</fr:em> when for any diagram <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathcal {I}}\xrightarrow {C_\bullet }{\mathcal {C}}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I}\xrightarrow {C_\bullet }\mathcal {C}\xrightarrow {F}\mathcal {D}]]></fr:tex> has a (co)limit, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_\bullet ]]></fr:tex> has a (co)limit that is both preserved and reflected by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
